of gluon force

01:00:25.720 --> 01:00:27.865
between the quark
and the anti-quark.

01:00:27.865 --> 01:00:29.490
And that would produce
a constant force

01:00:29.490 --> 01:00:32.970
no matter how far
apart you pulled them.

01:00:32.970 --> 01:00:34.680
And the only thing
that intervenes,

01:00:34.680 --> 01:00:36.870
and it is important
that it does intervene,

01:00:36.870 --> 01:00:39.480
is that if you pulled
them too far apart

01:00:39.480 --> 01:00:41.380
it would become
energetically favorable

01:00:41.380 --> 01:00:45.776
for a quark anti-quark pair
to materialize in the middle.

01:00:45.776 --> 01:00:48.150
And then instead of having a
quark here and an anti-quark

01:00:48.150 --> 01:00:50.112
here and a string
between them, you

01:00:50.112 --> 01:00:52.070
would have a quark here
and an anti-quark there

01:00:52.070 --> 01:00:55.140
and a string between them,
and an anti-quark here

01:00:55.140 --> 01:00:57.046
and-- I'm sorry, I
