01:00:57.046 --> 01:00:59.170
and an anti-quark there
and a string between those.

01:00:59.170 --> 01:01:01.160
And then they would
just fly apart.

01:01:01.160 --> 01:01:02.890
So the string can
break by producing

01:01:02.890 --> 01:01:04.210
quark anti-quark pairs.

01:01:04.210 --> 01:01:07.110
But the string can never just
end in the middle of nowhere.

01:01:07.110 --> 01:01:08.967
And that's the essence
of confinement.

01:01:08.967 --> 01:01:10.675
And it's due to the
peculiar interactions

01:01:10.675 --> 01:01:14.772
that these gluons
are believed to obey.

01:01:14.772 --> 01:01:16.230
So the gluons behave
in a way which

01:01:16.230 --> 01:01:18.490
is somewhat uncharacteristic
of particles.

01:01:18.490 --> 01:01:20.990
Except at very short distances,
they behave very much

01:01:20.990 --> 01:01:21.990
like ordinary particles.

01:01:21.990 --> 01:01:24.970
But at larger distances,
these effects of confinement

01:01:24.970 --> 01:01:28.570
play a very significant role.

01:01:28.570 --> 01:01:30.570
Any other questions?

01:01:30.570 --> 01:01:33.810
OK, onward, I want talk
about gauge theories,

01:01:33.810 --> 01:01:35.400
because gauge
theories have a lot

01:01:35.400 --> 01:01:38.530
to do with how one gets
into grand unified theories

01:01:38.530 --> 01:01:41.380
from the standard model.

01:01:41.380 --> 01:01:44.520
And, basically, a gauge
theory is a theory

01:01:44.520 --> 01:01:49.500
in which the fundamental fields
are not themselves reality.

01:01:49.500 --> 01:01:51.680
But rather there's a
set of transformations

01:01:51.680 --> 01:01:54.020
that the fields can
undergo which take you

01:01:54.020 --> 01:01:56.320
from one description
to an equivalent

01:01:56.320 --> 01:01:58.370
description of the same reality.

01:01:58.370 --> 01:01:59.940
So there's not a
one to one mapping

01:01:59.940 --> 01:02:01.490
between the fields and reality.

01:02:01.490 --> 01:02:03.364
There are many different
field configurations

01:02:03.364 --> 01:02:05.500
that correspond to
the same reality.

01:02:05.500 --> 01:02:07.560
And that's basically
what characterizes

01:02:07.560 --> 01:02:08.824
what we call a gauge theory.

01:02:08.824 --> 01:02:10.740
And you do know one
example of a gauge theory.

01:02:10.740 --> 01:02:12.896
And that's e and m.

01:02:12.896 --> 01:02:16.990
If e and m is expressed in terms
of the potentials Phi and A,

01:02:16.990 --> 01:02:19.120
you can write e in terms
of the potential that way

01:02:19.120 --> 01:02:23.140
and b as the curl of A, you
could put Phi and A together

01:02:23.140 --> 01:02:25.000
and make a four-vector
if you want

01:02:25.000 --> 01:02:28.052
to do things in a
Lorentz covariant way.

01:02:28.052 --> 01:02:30.260
And the important point,
though, whether you put them

01:02:30.260 --> 01:02:32.440
together or not, is
that you can always

01:02:32.440 --> 01:02:35.380
define a gauge transformation
depending on some arbitrary

01:02:35.380 --> 01:02:38.595
function Lambda, which is a
function of position and time.

01:02:38.595 --> 01:02:40.720
I didn't write in the
arguments, but Lambda is just

01:02:40.720 --> 01:02:43.190
an arbitrary function
of position and time.

01:02:43.190 --> 01:02:46.450
And for any Lambda you
can replace 5 by 5 prime,

01:02:46.450 --> 01:02:50.365
given by this line, and a by
a prime, given by that line.

01:02:50.365 --> 01:02:51.990
And if you go back
and compute e and b,

01:02:51.990 --> 01:02:53.860
you'll find that
they'll be unchanged.

01:02:53.860 --> 01:02:55.610
And therefore, the
physics is not changed,

01:02:55.610 --> 01:02:59.140
because the physics really
is all contained in e and b.

01:02:59.140 --> 01:03:01.590
So this gauge transformation
is a transformation

01:03:01.590 --> 01:03:04.570
on the fields of the theory--
it can be written covariantly

01:03:04.570 --> 01:03:08.065
this way-- which leaves
the physics invariant.

01:03:08.065 --> 01:03:09.940
And it turns out that
all the important field

01:03:09.940 --> 01:03:13.770
theories that we know
of are gauge theories.

01:03:13.770 --> 01:03:15.970
And that's why it's
worth mentioning here.

01:03:15.970 --> 01:03:20.290
Now, for e and m, the gauge
parameter is just this function

01:03:20.290 --> 01:03:23.087
Lambda, which is a function
of position and time.

01:03:23.087 --> 01:03:24.670
And an important
issue is what happens

01:03:24.670 --> 01:03:26.480
when you combine
gauge transformations,

01:03:26.480 --> 01:03:29.850
because the succession
of two transformations

01:03:29.850 --> 01:03:32.150
had better also be a
symmetry transformation.

01:03:32.150 --> 01:03:35.620
So it's worth understanding
that group structure.

01:03:35.620 --> 01:03:37.430
And for the case of e
and m, these Lambdas

01:03:37.430 --> 01:03:40.930
just add if we make
successive transformations.

01:03:40.930 --> 01:03:42.430
And that means the
group is Abelian.

01:03:42.430 --> 01:03:44.910
It's commutative.

01:03:44.910 --> 01:03:47.060
But that's not always the case.

01:03:47.060 --> 01:03:48.530
Let's see, where am I going?

01:03:48.530 --> 01:03:50.646
OK, next slide actually
comes somewhat later.

01:03:50.646 --> 01:03:52.020
Let me go back to
the blackboard.

01:03:57.100 --> 01:04:00.340
It turns out that the important
generalization of gauge

01:04:00.340 --> 01:04:03.710
theories is the generalization
from Abelian gauge

01:04:03.710 --> 01:04:06.680
theories to non-Abelian ones,
which was done originally

01:04:06.680 --> 01:04:16.130
by Yang and Mills
in 1954, I think.

01:04:16.130 --> 01:04:19.140
And when it was first proposed,
nobody knew what to do with it.

01:04:19.140 --> 01:04:21.310
But, ultimately, these
non-Abelian gauge theories

01:04:21.310 --> 01:04:26.170
became the standard model
of particle physics.

01:04:26.170 --> 01:04:28.570
And in non-Abelian
gauge theories

01:04:28.570 --> 01:04:31.720
the parameter that describes the
gauge transformation is a group

01:04:31.720 --> 01:04:35.850
element, not just
something that gets added.

01:04:35.850 --> 01:04:39.030
And group elements
multiply, according

01:04:39.030 --> 01:04:41.040
to the procedures of some group.

01:04:41.040 --> 01:04:43.772
And in particular,
the standard model

01:04:43.772 --> 01:04:44.980
is built out of three groups.

01:04:47.431 --> 01:04:49.430
And the fact that there
are three groups not one

01:04:49.430 --> 01:04:52.880
is just an example
of this ugliness

01:04:52.880 --> 01:04:54.980
that I mentioned and is
responsible for the fact

01:04:54.980 --> 01:04:58.470
that there's some significant
number of parameters

01:04:58.470 --> 01:05:01.120
even if there were no
other complications.

01:05:01.120 --> 01:05:07.460
So the standard model is based
on three gauge groups, SU3,

01:05:07.460 --> 01:05:10.370
SU2, and U1.

01:05:14.459 --> 01:05:16.250
And it won't really be
too important for us

01:05:16.250 --> 01:05:17.920
what exactly these groups are.

01:05:21.460 --> 01:05:25.280
Let me just mention
quickly, SU3 is a group of 3

01:05:25.280 --> 01:05:28.530
by 3 matrices which are
unitary in the sense

01:05:28.530 --> 01:05:33.130
that u adjoint times u is equal
to 1 and special in the sense

01:05:33.130 --> 01:05:35.390
that they have determinant 1.

01:05:35.390 --> 01:05:36.980
And the set of all
3 by 3 matrices

01:05:36.980 --> 01:05:38.438
have those properties
form a group.

01:05:38.438 --> 01:05:39.820
And that group is SU3.

01:05:39.820 --> 01:05:41.430
SU2 is the same
thing but replace

01:05:41.430 --> 01:05:44.400
the 3 in all those
sentences by 2s.

01:05:44.400 --> 01:05:47.306
U1 is just the group of phases.

01:05:47.306 --> 01:05:48.680
That is the group
of real numbers

01:05:48.680 --> 01:05:51.080
that could be written
as either the i phi.

01:05:51.080 --> 01:05:55.380
So it's just a complex number of
magnitude 1 with just a phase.

01:05:55.380 --> 01:05:58.510
And you can multiply those
and they form a group.

01:05:58.510 --> 01:06:00.740
And the standard model
contains these three groups.

01:06:00.740 --> 01:06:03.370
And the three groups
all act independently,

01:06:03.370 --> 01:06:05.952
which means that if you
know about group products,

01:06:05.952 --> 01:06:09.120
one can say that the full
group is the product group.

01:06:12.640 --> 01:06:16.670
And that just means that a full
description of a group element

01:06:16.670 --> 01:06:20.980
is really just a set
of an element of SU3,

01:06:20.980 --> 01:06:24.490
and an element of SU2,
and an element of U1.

01:06:24.490 --> 01:06:28.094
And if you put together three
group elements in each group

01:06:28.094 --> 01:06:29.510
and put them
together with commas,

01:06:29.510 --> 01:06:31.840
that becomes a group element
of the group SU3 cross,

01:06:31.840 --> 01:06:33.660
SU2 cross U1.

01:06:33.660 --> 01:06:37.322
And that is the gauge
group of the standard model

01:06:37.322 --> 01:06:38.155
of particle physics.

01:06:42.010 --> 01:07:08.050
OK, now grand unified theories,
a grand unified theory

01:07:08.050 --> 01:07:10.800
is based on the idea that
this set of three groups

01:07:10.800 --> 01:07:13.220
can all be embedded in
a single simple group.

01:07:37.760 --> 01:07:40.160
Now, simple actually has a
mathematical group theory

01:07:40.160 --> 01:07:40.660
meaning.

01:07:40.660 --> 01:07:42.660
But it also, for
our purposes, just

01:07:42.660 --> 01:07:46.580
means simple, which is
good enough for our brush

01:07:46.580 --> 01:07:49.220
through of these arguments.

01:07:49.220 --> 01:07:52.052
And, for example--
and the example

01:07:52.052 --> 01:07:54.010
is shown a little bit in
the lecture notes that

01:07:54.010 --> 01:07:57.900
will be posted
shortly-- an example

01:07:57.900 --> 01:07:59.570
of a grand unified
theory, and indeed

01:07:59.570 --> 01:08:02.070
the first grand unified
theory that was invented,

01:08:02.070 --> 01:08:06.260
is based on the full gauge group
SU5, which is just a group of 5

01:08:06.260 --> 01:08:10.750
by 5 matrices which are
unitary and have determinant 1.

01:08:10.750 --> 01:08:15.380
And there's an easy way to embed
SU3 and SU2 and U1 into SU5.

01:08:15.380 --> 01:08:17.490
And that's the way that
was used to construct

01:08:17.490 --> 01:08:19.930
this grand unified theory.

01:08:19.930 --> 01:08:29.200
One can take a 5 by 5 matrix--
so this is a 5 by 5 matrix--

01:08:29.200 --> 01:08:36.029
and one can simply take
the upper 3 by 3 block

01:08:36.029 --> 01:08:40.850
and put an SU3 matrix there.

01:08:40.850 --> 01:08:46.080
And one can take the
lower 2 by 2 block

01:08:46.080 --> 01:08:47.830
and put an SU2 matrix there.

01:08:51.840 --> 01:08:53.939
And then the U1 piece--
there's supposed

01:08:53.939 --> 01:08:57.359
to be a U1 left
over-- the U1 piece

01:08:57.359 --> 01:09:01.120
can be obtained by giving
an overall phase to this

01:09:01.120 --> 01:09:03.250
and an overall phase
to that in such a way

01:09:03.250 --> 01:09:05.590
that the product of
the five phases is 0.

01:09:05.590 --> 01:09:08.620
So the determinant
has not changed.

01:09:08.620 --> 01:09:17.660
So one can put an e to the i2
Phi there and a factor of e

01:09:17.660 --> 01:09:22.020
to the minus i3 Phi
there for any Phi.

01:09:24.810 --> 01:09:28.130
And then this Phi
becomes the description

01:09:28.130 --> 01:09:31.950
of the U1 piece of
this construction.

01:09:31.950 --> 01:09:35.020
So we can take an arbitrary
SU3 matrix, and arbitrary SU2

01:09:35.020 --> 01:09:39.240
matrix, and an arbitrary
U1 value expressed by Phi

01:09:39.240 --> 01:09:42.810
and put them together
to make an SU5 matrix.

01:09:42.810 --> 01:09:44.810
And if you think about
it, the SU3 piece

01:09:44.810 --> 01:09:47.634
will commute with the SU2
piece and with the U1 piece.

01:09:47.634 --> 01:09:49.800
These three pieces will all
commute with each other,

01:09:49.800 --> 01:09:51.341
if you think about
how multiplication

01:09:51.341 --> 01:09:52.620
works with this construction.

01:09:52.620 --> 01:09:53.953
So it does exactly what we want.

01:09:53.953 --> 01:09:57.310
It decomposes SU5.

01:09:57.310 --> 01:10:01.710
So it has a subgroup of
SU3 cross SU2 across U1.

01:10:01.710 --> 01:10:06.560
And that's how the simplest
grand unified theory works.

